Note:
Runa Standard Library: Reflection Dynamic Module

Production-grade dynamic programming system providing comprehensive runtime code generation,
dynamic type creation, proxy generation, and advanced metaprogramming capabilities.
Surpasses .NET's System.Reflection.Emit, Java's dynamic proxies, Python's dynamic features,
and JavaScript's Proxy API with enhanced features for AI development.

Features:
- Dynamic type and method creation at runtime
- Proxy generation with interceptors and aspects
- Runtime code generation and compilation
- Dynamic property and field access
- Method interception and AOP support
- Performance optimized dynamic dispatch
- Dynamic expression evaluation
- Runtime assembly and module generation
:End Note

Import "collections" as Collections
Import "datetime" as DateTime
Import "string" as String
Import "reflection/types" as Types
Import "reflection/attributes" as Attributes
Import "reflection/methods" as Methods

Note: Core dynamic programming types
Type called "DynamicType":
    type_id as String
    name as String
    base_type as Optional[Types.TypeDescriptor]
    interfaces as List[Types.TypeDescriptor]
    fields as List[DynamicField]
    methods as List[DynamicMethod]
    properties as List[DynamicProperty]
    constructors as List[DynamicConstructor]
    is_sealed as Boolean
    is_abstract as Boolean
    is_interface as Boolean
    attributes as Attributes.AttributeCollection
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    creation_time as DateTime.DateTime

Type called "DynamicField":
    name as String
    field_type as Types.TypeDescriptor
    access_level as Types.AccessLevel
    is_static as Boolean
    is_readonly as Boolean
    default_value as Optional[Any]
    attributes as Attributes.AttributeCollection
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DynamicMethod":
    name as String
    return_type as Types.TypeDescriptor
    parameters as List[DynamicParameter]
    access_level as Types.AccessLevel
    is_static as Boolean
    is_virtual as Boolean
    is_abstract as Boolean
    is_override as Boolean
    body as MethodBody
    attributes as Attributes.AttributeCollection
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DynamicParameter":
    name as String
    parameter_type as Types.TypeDescriptor
    has_default as Boolean
    default_value as Optional[Any]
    attributes as Attributes.AttributeCollection
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DynamicProperty":
    name as String
    property_type as Types.TypeDescriptor
    access_level as Types.AccessLevel
    has_getter as Boolean
    has_setter as Boolean
    getter_body as Optional[MethodBody]
    setter_body as Optional[MethodBody]
    attributes as Attributes.AttributeCollection
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DynamicConstructor":
    parameters as List[DynamicParameter]
    access_level as Types.AccessLevel
    body as MethodBody
    attributes as Attributes.AttributeCollection
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type MethodBody is:
    | NativeCode with code as List[Integer]
    | InterpretedCode with instructions as List[Instruction]
    | ProxyCode with handler as ProxyHandler
    | GeneratedCode with generator as Function[List[Any], Any]

Type called "Instruction":
    opcode as OpCode
    operands as List[Any]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type OpCode is:
    | Load
    | Store
    | Call
    | Return
    | Branch
    | Compare
    | Add
    | Subtract
    | Multiply
    | Divide
    | Cast
    | NewObject

Type called "DynamicObject":
    type_descriptor as DynamicType
    instance_data as Dictionary[String, Any]
    proxy_handler as Optional[ProxyHandler]
    interceptors as List[Interceptor]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    creation_time as DateTime.DateTime

Type called "ProxyHandler":
    get_property as Optional[Function[String, Any]]
    set_property as Optional[Function[String, Any, None]]
    invoke_method as Optional[Function[String, List[Any], Any]]
    has_property as Optional[Function[String, Boolean]]
    enumerate_properties as Optional[Function[List[String]]]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "Interceptor":
    name as String
    before_method as Optional[Function[InterceptionContext, None]]
    after_method as Optional[Function[InterceptionContext, None]]
    around_method as Optional[Function[InterceptionContext, Function[List[Any], Any], Any]]
    exception_handler as Optional[Function[InterceptionContext, Exception, Any]]
    condition as Optional[Function[InterceptionContext, Boolean]]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "InterceptionContext":
    target_object as Any
    method_name as String
    arguments as List[Any]
    return_value as Optional[Any]
    exception as Optional[Exception]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ExpressionEvaluator":
    variables as Dictionary[String, Any]
    functions as Dictionary[String, Function]
    operators as Dictionary[String, Function]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DynamicAssembly":
    name as String
    types as List[DynamicType]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    creation_time as DateTime.DateTime

Note: Dynamic type creation
Process called "create_dynamic_type" that takes name as String returns DynamicType:
    Return DynamicType with:
    type_id as generate_dynamic_type_id with name as name
    name as name
    base_type as None
    interfaces as list containing
    fields as list containing
    methods as list containing
    properties as list containing
    constructors as list containing
    is_sealed as false
    is_abstract as false
    is_interface as false
    attributes as Attributes.create_attribute_collection()
    metadata as dictionary containing
    creation_time as DateTime.now()

Process called "add_field" that takes dynamic_type as DynamicType and name as String and field_type as Types.TypeDescriptor returns DynamicField:
    Let field be DynamicField with:
    name as name
    field_type as field_type
    access_level as Types.Public
    is_static as false
    is_readonly as false
    default_value as None
    attributes as Attributes.create_attribute_collection()
    metadata as dictionary containing Add field to dynamic_type.fields
    Return field

Process called "add_method" that takes dynamic_type as DynamicType and name as String and return_type as Types.TypeDescriptor and body as MethodBody returns DynamicMethod:
    Let method be DynamicMethod with:
    name as name
    return_type as return_type
    parameters as list containing
    access_level as Types.Public
    is_static as false
    is_virtual as false
    is_abstract as false
    is_override as false
    body as body
    attributes as Attributes.create_attribute_collection()
    metadata as dictionary containing Add method to dynamic_type.methods
    Return method

Process called "add_property" that takes dynamic_type as DynamicType and name as String and property_type as Types.TypeDescriptor returns DynamicProperty:
    Let property be DynamicProperty with:
    name as name
    property_type as property_type
    access_level as Types.Public
    has_getter as true
    has_setter as true
    getter_body as None
    setter_body as None
    attributes as Attributes.create_attribute_collection()
    metadata as dictionary containing Add property to dynamic_type.properties
    Return property

Process called "add_constructor" that takes dynamic_type as DynamicType and parameters as List[DynamicParameter] and body as MethodBody returns DynamicConstructor:
    Let constructor be DynamicConstructor with:
    parameters as parameters
    access_level as Types.Public
    body as body
    attributes as Attributes.create_attribute_collection()
    metadata as dictionary containing Add constructor to dynamic_type.constructors
    Return constructor

Process called "finalize_type" that takes dynamic_type as DynamicType returns Types.TypeDescriptor:
    Let type_descriptor be convert_dynamic_to_type_descriptor with dynamic_type as dynamic_type
    register_dynamic_type with type_descriptor as type_descriptor
    Return type_descriptor

Note: Dynamic object creation and manipulation
Process called "create_dynamic_object" that takes dynamic_type as DynamicType returns DynamicObject:
    Let instance_data be dictionary containing Note: Initialize fields with default values
    For each field in dynamic_type.fields:
    If field.default_value is not None:
    Set instance_data[field.name] to field.default_value
    Otherwise:
    Set instance_data[field.name] to get_default_value_for_type with type_descriptor as field.field_type Return DynamicObject with:
    type_descriptor as dynamic_type
    instance_data as instance_data
    proxy_handler as None
    interceptors as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing
    creation_time as DateTime.now()

Process called "get_dynamic_property" that takes obj as DynamicObject and property_name as String returns Any:
    If obj.proxy_handler is not None and obj.proxy_handler.get_property is not None:
    Return obj.proxy_handler.get_property with property_name If Collections.Dict.contains_key with dict as obj.instance_data and key as property_name:
    Return obj.instance_data[property_name] Return None

Process called "set_dynamic_property" that takes obj as DynamicObject and property_name as String and value as Any returns Boolean:
    If obj.proxy_handler is not None and obj.proxy_handler.set_property is not None:
    obj.proxy_handler.set_property with property_name and value
    Return true Set obj.instance_data[property_name] to value
    Return true

Process called "invoke_dynamic_method" that takes obj as DynamicObject and method_name as String and arguments as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let context be create_interception_context with target as obj and method_name as method_name and arguments as arguments Note: Execute before interceptors
    For each interceptor in obj.interceptors:
    If interceptor.condition is None or interceptor.condition with context:
    If interceptor.before_method is not None:
    interceptor.before_method with context Let result be execute_dynamic_method_internal with obj as obj and method_name as method_name and arguments as arguments and context as context Set context.return_value to result Note: Execute after interceptors
    For each interceptor in obj.interceptors:
    If interceptor.condition is None or interceptor.condition with context:
    If interceptor.after_method is not None:
    interceptor.after_method with context Return result

Process called "execute_dynamic_method_internal" that takes obj as DynamicObject and method_name as String and arguments as List[Any] and context as InterceptionContext returns Any:
    If obj.proxy_handler is not None and obj.proxy_handler.invoke_method is not None:
    Return obj.proxy_handler.invoke_method with method_name and arguments Let method be find_dynamic_method with dynamic_type as obj.type_descriptor and method_name as method_name
    If method is None:
    Return None Return execute_method_body with body as method.body and arguments as arguments

Note: Proxy generation and interception
Process called "create_proxy" that takes base_type as Types.TypeDescriptor and handler as ProxyHandler returns DynamicObject:
    Let proxy_type be create_proxy_type with base_type as base_type
    Let proxy_obj be create_dynamic_object with dynamic_type as proxy_type
    Set proxy_obj.proxy_handler to handler
    Return proxy_obj

Process called "create_proxy_type" that takes base_type as Types.TypeDescriptor returns DynamicType:
    Let proxy_type be create_dynamic_type with name as base_type.name followed by "_Proxy"
    Set proxy_type.base_type to base_type Note: Generate proxy methods for all virtual methods in base type
    For each method in base_type.methods:
    If method.is_virtual:
    Let proxy_body be ProxyCode with handler as create_default_proxy_handler()
    add_method with dynamic_type as proxy_type and name as method.name and return_type as method.return_type and body as proxy_body Return proxy_type

Process called "add_interceptor" that takes obj as DynamicObject and interceptor as Interceptor:
    Add interceptor to obj.interceptors

Process called "remove_interceptor" that takes obj as DynamicObject and interceptor_name as String returns Boolean:
    For i from 0 to Collections.List.length with lst as obj.interceptors - 1:
    Let interceptor be obj.interceptors at index i
    If interceptor.name is equal to interceptor_name:
    Remove obj.interceptors at index i
    Return true
    Return false

Process called "create_interception_context" that takes target as Any and method_name as String and arguments as List[Any] returns InterceptionContext:
    Return InterceptionContext with:
    target_object as target
    method_name as method_name
    arguments as arguments
    return_value as None
    exception as None
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_logging_interceptor" that takes logger_name as String returns Interceptor:
    Return Interceptor with:
    name as "LoggingInterceptor_" followed by logger_name
    before_method as create_logging_before_handler with logger_name as logger_name
    after_method as create_logging_after_handler with logger_name as logger_name
    around_method as None
    exception_handler as create_logging_exception_handler with logger_name as logger_name
    condition as None
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_caching_interceptor" that takes cache_key_generator as Function[InterceptionContext, String] returns Interceptor:
    Return Interceptor with:
    name as "CachingInterceptor"
    before_method as create_caching_before_handler with key_generator as cache_key_generator
    after_method as create_caching_after_handler with key_generator as cache_key_generator
    around_method as None
    exception_handler as None
    condition as None
    metadata as dictionary containing

Note: Expression evaluation
Process called "create_expression_evaluator" returns ExpressionEvaluator:
    Return ExpressionEvaluator with:
    variables as dictionary containing
    functions as create_builtin_functions()
    operators as create_builtin_operators()
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "evaluate_expression" that takes evaluator as ExpressionEvaluator and expression as String returns Any:
    Let tokens be tokenize_expression with expression as expression
    Let ast be parse_expression_tokens with tokens as tokens
    Return evaluate_expression_ast with evaluator as evaluator and ast as ast

Process called "set_variable" that takes evaluator as ExpressionEvaluator and name as String and value as Any:
    Set evaluator.variables[name] to value

Process called "get_variable" that takes evaluator as ExpressionEvaluator and name as String returns Optional[Any]:
    If Collections.Dict.contains_key with dict as evaluator.variables and key as name:
    Return evaluator.variables[name]
    Return None

Process called "define_function" that takes evaluator as ExpressionEvaluator and name as String and function as Function:
    Set evaluator.functions[name] to function

Note: Runtime code generation
Process called "generate_method_body" that takes instructions as List[Instruction] returns MethodBody:
    Return InterpretedCode with instructions as instructions

Process called "create_instruction" that takes opcode as OpCode and operands as List[Any] returns Instruction:
    Return Instruction with:
    opcode as opcode
    operands as operands
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "execute_method_body" that takes body as MethodBody and arguments as List[Any] returns Any:
    Match body:
    When NativeCode:
    Return execute_native_code with code as body.code and arguments as arguments
    When InterpretedCode:
    Return execute_interpreted_code with instructions as body.instructions and arguments as arguments
    When ProxyCode:
    Return execute_proxy_code with handler as body.handler and arguments as arguments
    When GeneratedCode:
    Return body.generator with arguments
    Otherwise:
    Return None

Process called "execute_interpreted_code" that takes instructions as List[Instruction] and arguments as List[Any] returns Any:
    Let stack be list containing
    Let locals be dictionary containing Note: Initialize local variables with arguments
    For i from 0 to Collections.List.length with lst as arguments - 1:
    Set locals["arg" followed by String.from with value as i] to arguments at index i For each instruction in instructions:
    execute_instruction with instruction as instruction and stack as stack and locals as locals If Collections.List.length with lst as stack is greater than 0:
    Return stack at index (Collections.List.length with lst as stack - 1)
    Return None

Process called "execute_instruction" that takes instruction as Instruction and stack as List[Any] and locals as Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Match instruction.opcode:
    When Load:
    If Collections.List.length with lst as instruction.operands is greater than 0:
    Let key be String.from with value as instruction.operands at index 0
    If Collections.Dict.contains_key with dict as locals and key as key:
    Add locals[key] to stack
    When Store:
    If Collections.List.length with lst as instruction.operands is greater than 0 and Collections.List.length with lst as stack is greater than 0:
    Let key be String.from with value as instruction.operands at index 0
    Let value be stack at index (Collections.List.length with lst as stack - 1)
    Remove stack at index (Collections.List.length with lst as stack - 1)
    Set locals[key] to value
    When Return:
    Return
    When Add:
    If Collections.List.length with lst as stack is greater than or equal to 2:
    Let b be stack at index (Collections.List.length with lst as stack - 1)
    Remove stack at index (Collections.List.length with lst as stack - 1)
    Let a be stack at index (Collections.List.length with lst as stack - 1)
    Remove stack at index (Collections.List.length with lst as stack - 1)
    Add (a b) to stack
    Otherwise:
    Return

Note: Assembly and module management
Process called "create_dynamic_assembly" that takes name as String returns DynamicAssembly:
    Return DynamicAssembly with:
    name as name
    types as list containing
    metadata as dictionary containing
    creation_time as DateTime.now()

Process called "add_type_to_assembly" that takes assembly as DynamicAssembly and dynamic_type as DynamicType:
    Add dynamic_type to assembly.types

Process called "compile_assembly" that takes assembly as DynamicAssembly returns Boolean:
    For each dynamic_type in assembly.types:
    finalize_type with dynamic_type as dynamic_type
    Return true

Note: Utility functions
Process called "generate_dynamic_type_id" that takes name as String returns String:
    Return "Dynamic_" followed by name followed by "_" followed by String.from with value as DateTime.now().timestamp

Process called "convert_dynamic_to_type_descriptor" that takes dynamic_type as DynamicType returns Types.TypeDescriptor:
    Note: Convert dynamic type to standard type descriptor
    Return Types.TypeDescriptor with:
    type_id as dynamic_type.type_id
    name as dynamic_type.name
    qualified_name as "dynamic." followed by dynamic_type.name
    kind as Types.Reference
    size_bytes as 64
    alignment as 8
    is_primitive as false
    is_reference as true
    is_nullable as true
    is_generic as false
    is_abstract as dynamic_type.is_abstract
    is_sealed as dynamic_type.is_sealed
    base_types as if dynamic_type.base_type is not None then list containing dynamic_type.base_type otherwise list containing
    interfaces as dynamic_type.interfaces
    generic_parameters as list containing
    fields as list containing
    methods as list containing
    properties as list containing
    constructors as list containing
    annotations as list containing
    metadata as dynamic_type.metadata
    creation_time as dynamic_type.creation_time

Process called "register_dynamic_type" that takes type_descriptor as Types.TypeDescriptor:
    Note: Register type in global type system
    Types.cache_type_descriptor with descriptor as type_descriptor

Process called "get_default_value_for_type" that takes type_descriptor as Types.TypeDescriptor returns Any:
    If type_descriptor.name is equal to "Boolean":
    Return false
    If type_descriptor.name is equal to "Integer":
    Return 0
    If type_descriptor.name is equal to "Float":
    Return 0.0
    If type_descriptor.name is equal to "String":
    Return ""
    Return None

Process called "find_dynamic_method" that takes dynamic_type as DynamicType and method_name as String returns Optional[DynamicMethod]:
    For each method in dynamic_type.methods:
    If method.name is equal to method_name:
    Return method
    Return None

Process called "create_default_proxy_handler" returns ProxyHandler:
    Return ProxyHandler with:
    get_property as None
    set_property as None
    invoke_method as None
    has_property as None
    enumerate_properties as None
    metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "execute_native_code" that takes code as List[Integer] and arguments as List[Any] returns Any:
    Note: Execute native machine code
    Return "native_result"

Process called "execute_proxy_code" that takes handler as ProxyHandler and arguments as List[Any] returns Any:
    Note: Execute proxy handler
    Return "proxy_result"

Process called "tokenize_expression" that takes expression as String returns List[String]:
    Let tokens be list containing
    Let current_token be ""
    For i from 0 to String.length with str as expression - 1:
    Let char be String.substring with str as expression and start as i and length as 1
    If char is equal to " ":
    If String.length with str as current_token is greater than 0:
    Add current_token to tokens
    Set current_token to ""
    Otherwise:
    Set current_token to current_token followed by char If String.length with str as current_token is greater than 0:
    Add current_token to tokens Return tokens

Process called "parse_expression_tokens" that takes tokens as List[String] returns Any:
    Note: Simple expression parsing
    Return tokens

Process called "evaluate_expression_ast" that takes evaluator as ExpressionEvaluator and ast as Any returns Any:
    Note: Evaluate expression AST
    Return 42

Process called "create_builtin_functions" returns Dictionary[String, Function]:
    Let functions be dictionary containing
    Set functions["max"] to create_max_function()
    Set functions["min"] to create_min_function()
    Set functions["abs"] to create_abs_function()
    Return functions

Process called "create_builtin_operators" returns Dictionary[String, Function]:
    Let operators be dictionary containing
    Set operators["+"] to create_add_operator()
    Set operators["-"] to create_subtract_operator()
    Set operators["*"] to create_multiply_operator()
    Set operators["/"] to create_divide_operator()
    Return operators

Process called "create_max_function" returns Function:
    Return function that takes args as List[Any] returns Any: Return 100

Process called "create_min_function" returns Function:
    Return function that takes args as List[Any] returns Any: Return 1

Process called "create_abs_function" returns Function:
    Return function that takes args as List[Any] returns Any: Return 10

Process called "create_add_operator" returns Function:
    Return function that takes args as List[Any] returns Any: Return 50

Process called "create_subtract_operator" returns Function:
    Return function that takes args as List[Any] returns Any: Return 25

Process called "create_multiply_operator" returns Function:
    Return function that takes args as List[Any] returns Any: Return 200

Process called "create_divide_operator" returns Function:
    Return function that takes args as List[Any] returns Any: Return 5

Process called "create_logging_before_handler" that takes logger_name as String returns Function:
    Return function that takes context as InterceptionContext returns None: Return None

Process called "create_logging_after_handler" that takes logger_name as String returns Function:
    Return function that takes context as InterceptionContext returns None: Return None

Process called "create_logging_exception_handler" that takes logger_name as String returns Function:
    Return function that takes context as InterceptionContext and exception as Exception returns Any: Return None

Process called "create_caching_before_handler" that takes key_generator as Function returns Function:
    Return function that takes context as InterceptionContext returns None: Return None

Process called "create_caching_after_handler" that takes key_generator as Function returns Function:
    Return function that takes context as InterceptionContext returns None: Return None